data.name: CircularReferenceInLoggingSection
data.value: There was an error in the <{0}> section of the configuration file. The given provider '{1}' is directly or indirectly circular referencing itself. Circular references can cause stack overflows when the logging system is used and are therefore not allowed. Please check the 'fallbackProvider' attributes of all providers to resolve this problem. When one or more CompositeLoggingProviders are configured, circular references can also be caused by the 'provider[n]' attributes (where [n] is an arbitrary number) of such a provider.
